# Post-skew cooldown: records when each coin's p_price first entered an extreme
# (≥0.85 or ≤0.15). If the coin stays extreme for ≥5 minutes, it is stuck in a
# trending regime and all entries are blocked until p_price returns to 0.25–0.75.
# Macro-regime gate: if 3+ coins are simultaneously extreme for ≥60 s, that
# signals a broad crypto trend event — block ALL new entries.
_skew_extreme_since: dict = {}   # coin_id → epoch when it first went extreme

# Per-coin trend score: rolling mean |p_price − 0.5| over last 300 observations.
# 0.00 = maximally choppy (signals near 0.5), 0.50 = maximally trending (signals near 0/1).
# Gate fires when score ≥ 0.28 with ≥ 50 samples — coin is in a sustained directional move.
